<review_checklist>
1. TOPIC OVERLAP: Are there 2+ articles about essentially the same topic? (e.g. "weather warnings" + "weekend storms" = same topic). MERGE them into one comprehensive article.
2. CATEGORY BALANCE: Count categories (politics, economy, immigration, society, culture, sports, practical/utility, guide). Need at least 5 different categories. No category should have 3+ articles.
3. TYPE BALANCE: Max 2 utility/guide. At least 1 material (in-depth). Rest = news.
4. NO REPETITION: Check against recent articles (last 30 days). Remove anything too similar unless it's a genuine follow-up with NEW information.
5. GEOGRAPHIC DIVERSITY: Not only Lisbon — include Porto, Faro, Algarve, or national topics.
6. AUDIENCE RELEVANCE: Every article must matter to a Ukrainian immigrant. Remove overly local Portuguese topics that don't affect immigrants.
7. PRIORITY ORDER: Reorder by real importance. Breaking news first, evergreen guides last.

If the plan is already balanced, return it unchanged.
If you find problems, FIX them: merge duplicates, replace weak topics, reorder priorities.

Return the full corrected plan (all articles, not just changes).
</review_checklist>